Analog Input + Digital Output
In class activity (SOB 15 - Threshold)
 Use circuit you created in previous slide, no physical changes needed.
 Create a sketch code that will turn on the LED only when the LDR is fully covered
(tips: use conditional functionality).

Optional:
• Add an active buzzer on any digital pin on your Arduino
(buzzer does not need resistor, just be aware of the
polarity)
• Modify the code so the buzzer will sound when the LDR
is exposed to torch.